\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces \textbf  {Functionally decoupled ambiguity modeling in FDIL.} \textbf  {(a) The dual ambiguity challenge:} subjective visual intent recognition is fundamentally bottlenecked by \textit  {semantic ambiguity} (highly overlapping conceptual boundaries) and \textit  {supervisory ambiguity} (annotator disagreement and unstable training targets). \textbf  {(b) Functionally decoupled pipeline:} FDIL separates ambiguity-aware semantic refinement from ambiguity-aware semantic supervision. SLR-C builds a semantic prior from textual cues to provide structured candidate semantics, while UTD stabilizes learning under disagreement through rationale-guided text distillation and supports image-aware prediction on top of the semantic prior.}}{3}{}\protected@file@percent }
\providecommand*\caption@xref[2]{\@setref\relax\@undefined{#1}}
\newlabel{fig:teaser}{{1}{3}{}{figure.1}{}}
